{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01SPBrvsDvGkvzQRjcFa8E91","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01EAvpbsQgKzaaGcv6k2phhg","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/tmp/plan.md","content":"# MongoDB Replica Set — Change / Migration Plan\n\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-24  \n**Namespace:** `mongodb`  \n**Status:** REVIEW ONLY — no changes have been applied. The live cluster reflects\nthe baseline state documented here.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current State\n\n### 1.1 Replica Set Topology\n\n| Property | Value |\n|---|---|\n| Replica-set name | `mongodb-replica` |\n| Member count | 3 (all data-bearing, no arbiters) |\n| Protocol version | 1 (Raft) |\n| `writeConcernMajorityJournalDefault` | `true` |\n\n**Members** (all equal priority = 1, votes = 1, not hidden):\n\n| `_id` | Host |\n|---|---|\n| 0 | `mongodb-replica-0.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017` |\n| 1 | `mongodb-replica-1.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017` |\n| 2 | `mongodb-replica-2.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017` |\n\n**Replica-set settings (current):**\n\n| Setting | Current value |\n|---|---|\n| `heartbeatIntervalMillis` | 2000 |\n| `heartbeatTimeoutSecs` | 10 |\n| `electionTimeoutMillis` | 10000 |\n| `catchUpTimeoutMillis` | -1 (unlimited) |\n| `chainingAllowed` | true |\n| `getLastErrorDefaults` | `{ w: 1, wtimeout: 0 }` |\n\n### 1.2 Mongod Configuration (from ConfigMap `mongod-config`)\n\n| Category | Parameter | Current value |\n|---|---|---|\n| Storage / WiredTiger | `journalCompressor` | `zlib` |\n| Storage | `dbPath` | `/data/db` |\n| Network | `bindIpAll` | `true` |\n| Replication | `replSetName` | `mongodb-replica` |\n| Security | `authorization` | `enabled` |\n| Security | `keyFile` | `/etc/mongo-keyfile/keyfile` |\n| System log | `verbosity` | `1` (raised from default 0) |\n| Operation profiling | `mode` | `slowOp` |\n| Operation profiling | `slowOpThresholdMs` | `200` ms (tightened from default 100 ms) |\n\n### 1.3 Users and Roles\n\n| User | Auth DB | Roles |\n|---|---|---|\n| `admin-user` | `admin` | `clusterAdmin`, `userAdminAnyDatabase`, `readWriteAnyDatabase` |\n\nAuthentication mechanisms present on `admin-user`: `SCRAM-SHA-1` and\n`SCRAM-SHA-256`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Target Hardened Baseline\n\nThe following table describes the hardened target state. Changes are needed in\nthe areas marked **CHANGE**.\n\n| Area | Parameter | Current | Target | Action required |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| Network | `bindIpAll` | `true` | `false` with explicit `bindIp: 127.0.0.1,<pod-IP>` | **CHANGE** — avoid binding to all interfaces |\n| System log | `verbosity` | `1` | `0` (default) | **CHANGE** — revert to production-quiet logging |\n| Operation profiling | `slowOpThresholdMs` | `200` ms | `100` ms (MongoDB default) | **CHANGE** — restore default threshold |\n| Auth mechanisms | SCRAM-SHA-1 | enabled (present on admin-user) | disabled cluster-wide | **CHANGE** — disable legacy SCRAM-SHA-1 |\n| Write concern | `getLastErrorDefaults.w` | `1` | `majority` | **CHANGE** — enforce majority write concern |\n| Write concern | `getLastErrorDefaults.wtimeout` | `0` (unlimited) | `5000` ms | **CHANGE** — add a write-concern timeout |\n| Catch-up | `catchUpTimeoutMillis` | `-1` (unlimited) | `30000` ms | **CHANGE** — bound failover catch-up duration |\n| Role separation | `admin-user` has `readWriteAnyDatabase` | combined | split into dedicated app user + admin user | **CHANGE** — least-privilege separation |\n| TLS/mTLS | not configured | absent | TLS for client and intra-cluster traffic | **CHANGE** — add `net.tls` block |\n| Storage / journal | `journalCompressor` | `zlib` | `snappy` (lower CPU, similar ratio) | **CHANGE** if CPU budget is constrained; keep `zlib` otherwise |\n\n---\n\n## 3. Migration Steps\n\nExecute each step during the change window. Roll back by reverting the relevant\nConfigMap or `rs.reconfig()` call and performing a rolling restart.\n\n### Step 1 — Disable SCRAM-SHA-1\n\nSCRAM-SHA-1 is a weaker authentication mechanism. Remove it from the existing\nuser and set the cluster-wide `authenticationMechanisms` parameter to allow only\n`SCRAM-SHA-256`.\n\n```javascript\n// On the PRIMARY — run once\ndb.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").updateUser(\"admin-user\", {\n  mechanisms: [\"SCRAM-SHA-256\"]\n})\n```\n\nThen add to `mongod.conf` under `security:`:\n\n```yaml\nsecurity:\n  authorization: enabled\n  keyFile: /etc/mongo-keyfile/keyfile\n  authenticationMechanisms: SCRAM-SHA-256\n```\n\nApply via rolling restart (Step 6).\n\n### Step 2 — Add TLS for Client and Intra-Cluster Traffic\n\nCreate a TLS Secret containing the CA certificate, the server certificate, and\nthe private key (one cert per node or a wildcard SAN cert covering all pod DNS\nnames). Mount it into each pod.\n\nAdd to `mongod.conf`:\n\n```yaml\nnet:\n  bindIp: 127.0.0.1  # refined in Step 3\n  tls:\n    mode: requireTLS\n    certificateKeyFile: /etc/mongo-tls/tls.pem\n    CAFile: /etc/mongo-tls/ca.crt\n    clusterAuthMode: x509   # or keep keyFile + requireTLS for intra-cluster\n```\n\nUpdate the StatefulSet to mount the TLS Secret at `/etc/mongo-tls/`.\n\n### Step 3 — Restrict Network Binding\n\nReplace `bindIpAll: true` with an explicit bind list:\n\n```yaml\nnet:\n  bindIp: \"127.0.0.1\"   # TLS listener added by mongo automatically on pod IP when tls.mode != disabled\n```\n\nIf TLS is not being added in this window, pin to the pod's IP explicitly:\n\n```yaml\nnet:\n  bindIp: \"127.0.0.1,$(MY_POD_IP)\"\n```\n\nExpose `MY_POD_IP` via the Downward API in the StatefulSet `env:` block.\n\n### Step 4 — Tighten Replica-Set Write-Concern and Catch-Up Defaults\n\nRun `rs.reconfig()` on the primary (no rolling restart required for settings-only\nchanges):\n\n```javascript\ncfg = rs.conf()\ncfg.settings.getLastErrorDefaults = { w: \"majority\", wtimeout: 5000 }\ncfg.settings.catchUpTimeoutMillis = 30000\nrs.reconfig(cfg)\n```\n\nVerify with `rs.conf().settings`.\n\n### Step 5 — Separate Admin and Application Users (Least Privilege)\n\n`admin-user` currently combines cluster-admin, user-admin, and read-write\ndatabase roles. Separate these into dedicated accounts:\n\n```javascript\n// Create a dedicated DBA account (admin actions only)\ndb.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").createUser({\n  user: \"dba\",\n  pwd: \"<strong-generated-password>\",\n  mechanisms: [\"SCRAM-SHA-256\"],\n  roles: [\n    { role: \"clusterAdmin\",        db: \"admin\" },\n    { role: \"userAdminAnyDatabase\",db: \"admin\" }\n  ]\n})\n\n// Create a per-application account (example: app \"myapp\")\ndb.getSiblingDB(\"myapp\").createUser({\n  user: \"myapp-svc\",\n  pwd: \"<strong-generated-password>\",\n  mechanisms: [\"SCRAM-SHA-256\"],\n  roles: [{ role: \"readWrite\", db: \"myapp\" }]\n})\n\n// After confirming new accounts work, remove readWriteAnyDatabase from admin-user\ndb.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").updateUser(\"admin-user\", {\n  roles: [\n    { role: \"clusterAdmin\",        db: \"admin\" },\n    { role: \"userAdminAnyDatabase\",db: \"admin\" }\n  ]\n})\n```\n\nStore new credentials in Kubernetes Secrets; update application connection\nstrings.\n\n### Step 6 — Update ConfigMap and Perform Rolling Restart\n\nAfter all `mongod.conf` changes are finalised, update the `mongod-config`\nConfigMap. The target `mongod.conf` is:\n\n```yaml\nstorage:\n  dbPath: /data/db\n  wiredTiger:\n    engineConfig:\n      journalCompressor: zlib          # keep unless CPU profiling dictates snappy\n\nnet:\n  bindIp: \"127.0.0.1\"                 # Step 3 — no longer bindIpAll\n  tls:\n    mode: requireTLS                   # Step 2\n    certificateKeyFile: /etc/mongo-tls/tls.pem\n    CAFile: /etc/mongo-tls/ca.crt\n\nreplication:\n  replSetName: mongodb-replica\n\nsecurity:\n  authorization: enabled\n  keyFile: /etc/mongo-keyfile/keyfile\n  authenticationMechanisms: SCRAM-SHA-256   # Step 1\n\nsystemLog:\n  verbosity: 0                         # Step — revert to production default\n\noperationProfiling:\n  mode: slowOp\n  slowOpThresholdMs: 100               # Step — restore default threshold\n```\n\nApply the rolling restart (one pod at a time, starting from secondaries):\n\n```bash\n# Restart each secondary first, then primary\nkubectl -n mongodb rollout restart statefulset/mongodb-replica\n# Monitor:\nkubectl -n mongodb rollout status statefulset/mongodb-replica\n```\n\nVerify health after each pod comes back:\n\n```javascript\nrs.status()          // all members SECONDARY or PRIMARY, no RECOVERING > 30 s\ndb.adminCommand({ ping: 1 })\n```\n\n### Step 7 — (Optional) Switch Journal Compressor to snappy\n\nIf CPU profiling during Step 6 shows compression overhead is unacceptable,\nchange `journalCompressor: zlib` to `journalCompressor: snappy` and perform\nanother rolling restart. `snappy` has lower CPU cost with only slightly larger\njournal files.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Rollback Procedure\n\nFor each step:\n\n| Step | Rollback |\n|---|---|\n| 1 (SCRAM-SHA-1) | `updateUser` to re-add `SCRAM-SHA-1`; remove `authenticationMechanisms` from conf; rolling restart |\n| 2 (TLS) | Remove `net.tls` block; rolling restart |\n| 3 (bindIp) | Restore `bindIpAll: true`; rolling restart |\n| 4 (write-concern) | `rs.reconfig()` restoring original `getLastErrorDefaults` and `catchUpTimeoutMillis` |\n| 5 (users) | Re-add `readWriteAnyDatabase` to `admin-user`; drop new accounts if unused |\n| 6 (ConfigMap) | `kubectl apply` the original ConfigMap; rolling restart |\n\n---\n\n## 5. Risks and Notes\n\n- **keyFile vs. x509 intra-cluster auth:** Step 2 shows `keyFile` kept alongside\n  TLS. Migrating intra-cluster auth to x509 (mutual TLS) is a two-phase process\n  (add `sendKeyFile`, then `sendX509`, then `x509`) and should be scheduled as a\n  separate change window.\n- **`catchUpTimeoutMillis = 30000`:** Bounding catch-up means that after a\n  failover, a new primary may step up before fully caught up. The `majority` write\n  concern in Step 4 mitigates data-loss risk.\n- **`slowOpThresholdMs` regression to 100 ms:** This reverts the tightened\n  threshold. If the team wants to retain 200 ms or set a different value, update\n  Step 6 accordingly.\n- **StatefulSet rolling restart ordering:** Kubernetes rolls pods in reverse-index\n  order (2 → 1 → 0). Pod 0 is typically the primary; it will be restarted last,\n  triggering one election. The replica set will remain available throughout.\n- **No CRDs or operators:** All steps use `mongosh`, `kubectl`, and native\n  ConfigMap updates as required by the task constraints.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1273,"cache_read_input_tokens":31810,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1273},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bc735346-6c07-4e80-87dd-0409524b961f","uuid":"f54e0cdd-743f-4ecb-b12b-6d8bb6ce2344","request_id":"req_011CcMWz1vKHrEDZisrAM45k"}
