{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01YaPxYTRu1zqoBPKZFaKcrH","type":"tool_result","content":"# Elasticsearch Cluster Change & Migration Plan\n\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-24  \n**Cluster:** es-cluster (namespace: elasticsearch)  \n**Current Version:** 8.11.1  \n**Status:** Planning only — no live changes are to be applied until this plan is reviewed and approved.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current State Inventory\n\n### 1.1 Topology\n\n| Component | Detail |\n|-----------|--------|\n| Nodes | 3 (es-cluster-0, es-cluster-1, es-cluster-2) |\n| Node roles | `master`, `data`, `ingest` (all combined on every node) |\n| Node attribute | `node.attr.tier: hot` |\n| Elasticsearch version | 8.11.1 (build 2023-11-11) |\n| Lucene version | 9.8.0 |\n| JVM version | OpenJDK 21.0.1 (bundled) |\n| Image | docker.elastic.co/elasticsearch/elasticsearch:8.11.1 |\n| Cluster UUID | 5GzFhd9CQsetEnXzFEQeQg |\n| Cluster health | green |\n| Minimum wire compat | 7.17.0 |\n| Minimum index compat | 7.0.0 |\n\n### 1.2 Kubernetes Resources\n\n| Resource | Detail |\n|----------|--------|\n| Kind | StatefulSet (Parallel pod management) |\n| Update strategy | **OnDelete** (pods must be deleted manually to trigger updates) |\n| Replicas | 3/3 ready |\n| CPU request / limit | 500m / 1 |\n| Memory request / limit | 1 Gi / 2 Gi |\n| JVM heap | -Xms512m -Xmx512m (512 MB fixed) |\n| PVC per node | 5 Gi ReadWriteOnce |\n| PVC disk used | ~1.3 KB (audit-index only; ~910 GB free of ~1.1 TB) |\n| Services | es-http (ClusterIP :9200), es-cluster (headless :9300) |\n\n### 1.3 elasticsearch.yml (ConfigMap: es-config)\n\n```yaml\ncluster.name: es-cluster\nnode.name: ${POD_NAME}\nnode.roles: [ master, data, ingest ]\nnode.attr.tier: hot\nnetwork.host: 0.0.0.0\ndiscovery.seed_hosts:\n  - es-cluster-0.es-cluster\n  - es-cluster-1.es-cluster\n  - es-cluster-2.es-cluster\ncluster.initial_master_nodes:\n  - es-cluster-0\n  - es-cluster-1\n  - es-cluster-2\nnode.store.allow_mmap: false\nxpack.security.enabled: false\nxpack.security.http.ssl.enabled: false\nxpack.security.transport.ssl.enabled: false\n```\n\n### 1.4 Indices\n\n| Index | Shards | Replicas | Docs | Size | Notes |\n|-------|--------|----------|------|------|-------|\n| audit-index | 3 primary | 1 | 0 | 1.3 KB | routing.allocation.require.tier=hot; _tier_preference=data_content |\n\n**Shard placement (current):**\n\n| Shard | Primary node | Replica node |\n|-------|-------------|-------------|\n| audit-index/0 | es-cluster-2 | es-cluster-0 |\n| audit-index/1 | es-cluster-0 | es-cluster-1 |\n| audit-index/2 | es-cluster-2 | es-cluster-1 |\n\n### 1.5 Index Settings (Non-Default)\n\n`audit-index` has the following non-default allocation settings:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"index.routing.allocation.include._tier_preference\": \"data_content\",\n  \"index.routing.allocation.require.tier\": \"hot\"\n}\n```\n\n`require.tier: hot` hard-pins all shards to nodes bearing `node.attr.tier=hot`. All three current nodes carry this attribute, so the constraint is satisfied. During any topology change (adding non-hot nodes or removing the attribute), this constraint must be re-evaluated before shards will allocate.\n\n### 1.6 Cluster Settings\n\n- **Persistent settings:** none configured (all defaults)\n- **Transient settings:** none configured (all defaults)\n- Notable defaults active:\n  - `cluster.routing.allocation.disk.watermark.low: 85%`\n  - `cluster.routing.allocation.disk.watermark.high: 90%`\n  - `cluster.routing.allocation.disk.watermark.flood_stage: 95%`\n  - `cluster.max_shards_per_node: 1000`\n  - `action.destructive_requires_name: true`\n\n### 1.7 ILM Policies\n\nAll policies present are built-in managed policies (`_meta.managed: true`). **None are currently in use** by any index or data stream. Custom policies: none.\n\n| Policy | Hot rollover | Warm | Delete |\n|--------|-------------|------|--------|\n| .monitoring-8-ilm-policy | 3d / 50 GB | forcemerge | 3d |\n| behavioral_analytics-events-default_policy | 30d / 50 GB | 2d forcemerge+shrink | 180d |\n| ilm-history-ilm-policy | 30d / 50 GB | — | 90d |\n| ml-size-based-ilm-policy | 50 GB | — | — |\n\n### 1.8 Index Templates\n\nOnly built-in managed templates exist (`.kibana-reporting`, `.watch-history-16`, etc.). No custom index templates are present.\n\n### 1.9 Security\n\n| Setting | Value | Risk |\n|---------|-------|------|\n| xpack.security.enabled | **false** | CRITICAL — no authentication |\n| xpack.security.http.ssl.enabled | **false** | CRITICAL — plaintext HTTP |\n| xpack.security.transport.ssl.enabled | **false** | CRITICAL — plaintext inter-node |\n\nThe cluster is fully open: any pod in the cluster can read, write, or delete all data without credentials.\n\n### 1.10 Snapshot Repositories\n\n**None configured.** There is no backup target for the cluster.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Issues Requiring Action Before Upgrade\n\n### CRITICAL\n\n1. **No snapshot repository**: Upgrades are irreversible at the index compatibility level. A full snapshot must be taken and verified before any upgrade step is attempted.\n\n2. **Security disabled**: `xpack.security.enabled: false` is not acceptable for production. Enabling security requires a full rolling restart and TLS certificate provisioning. This should be done as a standalone change before the version upgrade to keep rollback windows clean.\n\n3. **`cluster.initial_master_nodes` still set**: This setting is only for first-time bootstrap and must be removed from `elasticsearch.yml` after initial cluster formation. Leaving it set can cause split-brain issues if a quorum is lost and nodes are restarted. It does not prevent normal operation but creates operational risk.\n\n### HIGH\n\n4. **JVM heap at 512 MB**: Elasticsearch recommends heap ≤ 50% of available RAM, minimum 1 GB for production. At 2 Gi container limit, the recommended setting is `-Xms1g -Xmx1g`. At 512 MB, GC pressure increases significantly under any indexing load.\n\n5. **PVC at 5 Gi**: Currently near-empty, but 5 Gi is far below any production sizing for an audit log index. Plan for PVC expansion before data volume grows; PVC expansion requires StorageClass support for `allowVolumeExpansion`.\n\n6. **`updateStrategy: OnDelete`**: Rolling upgrades are fully manual — each pod must be deleted one at a time. Consider switching to `RollingUpdate` with `maxUnavailable: 1` for automated, ordered upgrades (requires Kubernetes 1.22+).\n\n### MEDIUM\n\n7. **All nodes are combined-role**: No dedicated master nodes. With 3 combined nodes, losing 2 simultaneously loses both quorum and all data capacity. For production, dedicated master-eligible nodes (3 or 5) with separate data nodes are recommended.\n\n8. **`node.store.allow_mmap: false`**: Disables memory-mapped files, which reduces performance. The `vm.max_map_count` kernel parameter (`sysctl -w vm.max_map_count=262144`) should be set via an `initContainer` or node configuration, then this flag should be removed to re-enable mmap.\n\n9. **No monitoring**: The `.monitoring-8-ilm-policy` policy exists but no monitoring data streams are active. Upgrade visibility requires monitoring of indexing rate, heap usage, GC time, and shard counts.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Migration Plan: Security Enablement (Pre-Upgrade)\n\n**Goal:** Enable xpack security and TLS without changing data or cluster version.  \n**Requires:** Rolling restart (one pod at a time); cluster stays green throughout.\n\n### Step 3.1 — Generate TLS certificates\n\n```bash\n# Run on a temporary pod or locally with elasticsearch-certutil\ndocker run --rm -v $(pwd)/certs:/certs \\\n  docker.elastic.co/elasticsearch/elasticsearch:8.11.1 \\\n  bin/elasticsearch-certutil ca --out /certs/elastic-stack-ca.p12 --pass \"\"\n\ndocker run --rm -v $(pwd)/certs:/certs \\\n  docker.elastic.co/elasticsearch/elasticsearch:8.11.1 \\\n  bin/elasticsearch-certutil cert --ca /certs/elastic-stack-ca.p12 --ca-pass \"\" \\\n  --out /certs/elastic-certificates.p12 --pass \"\"\n```\n\n### Step 3.2 — Create Kubernetes Secret\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n elasticsearch create secret generic es-certs \\\n  --from-file=elastic-certificates.p12=./certs/elastic-certificates.p12 \\\n  --from-file=elastic-stack-ca.p12=./certs/elastic-stack-ca.p12\n```\n\n### Step 3.3 — Update elasticsearch.yml ConfigMap\n\nRemove `cluster.initial_master_nodes` and enable security:\n\n```yaml\ncluster.name: es-cluster\nnode.name: ${POD_NAME}\nnode.roles: [ master, data, ingest ]\nnode.attr.tier: hot\nnetwork.host: 0.0.0.0\ndiscovery.seed_hosts:\n  - es-cluster-0.es-cluster\n  - es-cluster-1.es-cluster\n  - es-cluster-2.es-cluster\n# cluster.initial_master_nodes: REMOVED after initial bootstrap\nnode.store.allow_mmap: false\nxpack.security.enabled: true\nxpack.security.http.ssl.enabled: true\nxpack.security.http.ssl.keystore.path: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/elastic-certificates.p12\nxpack.security.transport.ssl.enabled: true\nxpack.security.transport.ssl.verification_mode: certificate\nxpack.security.transport.ssl.keystore.path: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/elastic-certificates.p12\nxpack.security.transport.ssl.truststore.path: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/elastic-stack-ca.p12\n```\n\n### Step 3.4 — Update StatefulSet to mount certs and fix heap\n\nAdd to the container spec:\n\n```yaml\nenv:\n- name: ES_JAVA_OPTS\n  value: \"-Xms1g -Xmx1g\"   # increased from 512m\nvolumeMounts:\n- name: es-certs\n  mountPath: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs\n  readOnly: true\nvolumes:\n- name: es-certs\n  secret:\n    secretName: es-certs\n```\n\n### Step 3.5 — Set built-in passwords (post-restart)\n\nAfter the first node restarts with security enabled, set the built-in user passwords:\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n elasticsearch exec es-cluster-0 -- \\\n  bin/elasticsearch-setup-passwords auto\n# Store output passwords in a secrets manager\n```\n\n### Step 3.6 — Rolling restart (OnDelete strategy)\n\n```bash\n# Delete one pod at a time; wait for green before proceeding to next\nkubectl -n elasticsearch delete pod es-cluster-2\n# Wait: kubectl -n elasticsearch exec curl-test -- \\\n#   curl -su elastic:<pass> \"https://es-http:9200/_cluster/health?wait_for_status=green&timeout=120s\"\nkubectl -n elasticsearch delete pod es-cluster-1\n# Wait for green\nkubectl -n elasticsearch delete pod es-cluster-0\n# Wait for green\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. Migration Plan: Version Upgrade 8.11.1 → 8.17.x\n\n**Target version:** 8.17.x (latest 8.x stable as of plan date)  \n**Minimum path:** Single-hop upgrade within 8.x is supported (no intermediate version needed).  \n**Wire compatibility:** 8.x nodes are wire-compatible with 7.17+ nodes. A mixed 8.x cluster is valid during rolling upgrade.\n\n### Step 4.1 — Prerequisite gate (all must pass)\n\n- [ ] Snapshot repository registered and snapshot verified restorable\n- [ ] Cluster health is green\n- [ ] No unassigned shards\n- [ ] Security enabled (TLS + authentication active)\n- [ ] `cluster.initial_master_nodes` removed from config\n- [ ] All pending tasks drained (`number_of_pending_tasks == 0`)\n- [ ] Deprecation API clean (no upgrade-blocking deprecations):\n\n```bash\ncurl -su elastic:<pass> \"https://es-http:9200/_migration/deprecations\"\n```\n\n### Step 4.2 — Disable shard rebalancing\n\n```bash\ncurl -su elastic:<pass> -X PUT \"https://es-http:9200/_cluster/settings\" \\\n  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{\n  \"persistent\": {\n    \"cluster.routing.allocation.enable\": \"primaries\"\n  }\n}'\n```\n\nThis prevents unnecessary shard movement during the rolling restart.\n\n### Step 4.3 — Update the StatefulSet image\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n elasticsearch set image statefulset/es-cluster \\\n  elasticsearch=docker.elastic.co/elasticsearch/elasticsearch:8.17.6\n```\n\nWith `updateStrategy: OnDelete`, this only updates the template — no pods restart yet.\n\n### Step 4.4 — Rolling pod replacement (one at a time)\n\nFor each node, starting with a non-master (any non-elected-master node):\n\n```bash\n# Identify current master first\ncurl -su elastic:<pass> \"https://es-http:9200/_cat/master?v\"\n\n# Upgrade non-master nodes first; master last\nkubectl -n elasticsearch delete pod es-cluster-2\n# Poll until green AND es-cluster-2 is back and running 8.17.x:\nkubectl -n elasticsearch exec curl-test -- \\\n  curl -su elastic:<pass> \\\n  \"https://es-http:9200/_cat/nodes?v&h=name,version,master\"\n# Repeat for es-cluster-1, then es-cluster-0 (if master)\n```\n\n### Step 4.5 — Re-enable shard allocation\n\n```bash\ncurl -su elastic:<pass> -X PUT \"https://es-http:9200/_cluster/settings\" \\\n  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{\n  \"persistent\": {\n    \"cluster.routing.allocation.enable\": null\n  }\n}'\n```\n\n### Step 4.6 — Post-upgrade validation\n\n```bash\n# All nodes on new version\ncurl -su elastic:<pass> \"https://es-http:9200/_cat/nodes?v&h=name,version,master\"\n\n# Cluster health green\ncurl -su elastic:<pass> \"https://es-http:9200/_cluster/health?pretty\"\n\n# audit-index still has all shards allocated\ncurl -su elastic:<pass> \"https://es-http:9200/_cat/shards?v\"\n\n# Index settings preserved\ncurl -su elastic:<pass> \"https://es-http:9200/audit-index/_settings?pretty\"\n\n# No deprecation warnings blocking future upgrades\ncurl -su elastic:<pass> \"https://es-http:9200/_migration/deprecations\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. Additional Recommended Changes (Post-Upgrade)\n\n### 5.1 Switch UpdateStrategy to RollingUpdate\n\n```yaml\nupdateStrategy:\n  type: RollingUpdate\n  rollingUpdate:\n    maxUnavailable: 1\n```\n\nThis enables ordered, automated rolling upgrades in future cycles.\n\n### 5.2 Enable mmap for performance\n\nAdd an `initContainer` to set the kernel parameter:\n\n```yaml\ninitContainers:\n- name: set-vm-max-map-count\n  image: busybox\n  command: ['sysctl', '-w', 'vm.max_map_count=262144']\n  securityContext:\n    privileged: true\n```\n\nThen remove `node.store.allow_mmap: false` from elasticsearch.yml.\n\n### 5.3 Register a snapshot repository\n\nBefore any future upgrade, register a repository (S3, GCS, or a shared PVC):\n\n```bash\ncurl -su elastic:<pass> -X PUT \"https://es-http:9200/_snapshot/backups\" \\\n  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{\n  \"type\": \"fs\",\n  \"settings\": {\n    \"location\": \"/mnt/snapshots\"\n  }\n}'\n```\n\nCreate a Snapshot Lifecycle Management (SLM) policy for daily automated snapshots.\n\n### 5.4 Assign an ILM policy to audit-index\n\nCurrently `audit-index` has no ILM lifecycle. An audit index will grow unbounded. Assign a policy that rolls over at size/age and deletes old indices:\n\n```bash\n# Create policy\ncurl -su elastic:<pass> -X PUT \"https://es-http:9200/_ilm/policy/audit-policy\" \\\n  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{\n  \"policy\": {\n    \"phases\": {\n      \"hot\": { \"actions\": { \"rollover\": { \"max_age\": \"30d\", \"max_primary_shard_size\": \"10gb\" } } },\n      \"delete\": { \"min_age\": \"90d\", \"actions\": { \"delete\": {} } }\n    }\n  }\n}'\n# Apply to index template for audit-index\n```\n\n### 5.5 PVC expansion planning\n\nPVC expansion (if StorageClass supports it) can be done in-place:\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n elasticsearch patch pvc data-es-cluster-0 \\\n  -p '{\"spec\":{\"resources\":{\"requests\":{\"storage\":\"50Gi\"}}}}'\n# Repeat for data-es-cluster-1, data-es-cluster-2\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. Risk Assessment\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|-----------|--------|-----------|\n| Shard unavailability during restart | Low | Medium | OnDelete strategy, wait-for-green between pods |\n| Data loss on upgrade failure | Low | High | Snapshot before any change; verify restore |\n| Security enablement causes auth failure | Medium | High | Test with one pod first; keep a known-good password reference |\n| PVC too small for audit data growth | High | Medium | Plan expansion before index grows; 5 Gi is near-empty now |\n| Split-brain from initial_master_nodes misconfiguration | Low | Critical | Remove setting from config in Step 3.3 |\n| JVM GC pauses under load at 512m heap | High | Medium | Increase to 1g in same config change as security |\n\n---\n\n## 7. Rollback Plan\n\n### Rollback from security change\n\nRevert the es-config ConfigMap to the original (security disabled), delete each pod one at a time. Cluster will restart without authentication.\n\n### Rollback from version upgrade\n\nElasticsearch does **not** support downgrading a node once data has been written with a newer Lucene version. The only rollback path is:\n\n1. Stop all 8.17.x pods.\n2. Restore from the pre-upgrade snapshot into a fresh 8.11.1 cluster.\n3. This is why Step 4.1 (snapshot gate) is non-negotiable.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Change Order Summary\n\n| # | Change | Type | Requires Restart | Approval Gate |\n|---|--------|------|-----------------|---------------|\n| 1 | Configure snapshot repository + take snapshot | Live API | No | SRE lead |\n| 2 | Remove cluster.initial_master_nodes from config | Config change | Yes (rolling) | SRE lead |\n| 3 | Increase JVM heap to 1g | Config change | Yes (rolling) | SRE lead |\n| 4 | Provision TLS certs + enable xpack.security | Config + Secret | Yes (rolling) | Security team + SRE lead |\n| 5 | Set built-in user passwords | API call | No | SRE lead |\n| 6 | Upgrade image 8.11.1 → 8.17.x | Image update | Yes (rolling) | Change advisory board |\n| 7 | Enable mmap via initContainer | Config + STS | Yes (rolling) | SRE lead |\n| 8 | Switch to RollingUpdate strategy | STS spec | No | SRE lead |\n| 9 | Add ILM policy to audit-index | API call | No | SRE lead |\n| 10 | Expand PVCs | PVC patch | No | Storage team |\n\n---\n\n*This plan is for review only. No changes have been or will be applied to the live cluster until this document is approved by the SRE lead and, for changes 4 and 6, the relevant approval gates.*","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bc735346-6c07-4e80-87dd-0409524b961f","uuid":"a46bb09b-610f-4005-b83b-bab741fb4dae","timestamp":"2026-06-24T05:18:07.792Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"# Elasticsearch Cluster Change & Migration Plan\n\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-24  \n**Cluster:** es-cluster (namespace: elasticsearch)  \n**Current Version:** 8.11.1  \n**Status:** Planning only — no live changes are to be applied until this plan is reviewed and approved.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current State Inventory\n\n### 1.1 Topology\n\n| Component | Detail |\n|-----------|--------|\n| Nodes | 3 (es-cluster-0, es-cluster-1, es-cluster-2) |\n| Node roles | `master`, `data`, `ingest` (all combined on every node) |\n| Node attribute | `node.attr.tier: hot` |\n| Elasticsearch version | 8.11.1 (build 2023-11-11) |\n| Lucene version | 9.8.0 |\n| JVM version | OpenJDK 21.0.1 (bundled) |\n| Image | docker.elastic.co/elasticsearch/elasticsearch:8.11.1 |\n| Cluster UUID | 5GzFhd9CQsetEnXzFEQeQg |\n| Cluster health | green |\n| Minimum wire compat | 7.17.0 |\n| Minimum index compat | 7.0.0 |\n\n### 1.2 Kubernetes Resources\n\n| Resource | Detail |\n|----------|--------|\n| Kind | StatefulSet (Parallel pod management) |\n| Update strategy | **OnDelete** (pods must be deleted manually to trigger updates) |\n| Replicas | 3/3 ready |\n| CPU request / limit | 500m / 1 |\n| Memory request / limit | 1 Gi / 2 Gi |\n| JVM heap | -Xms512m -Xmx512m (512 MB fixed) |\n| PVC per node | 5 Gi ReadWriteOnce |\n| PVC disk used | ~1.3 KB (audit-index only; ~910 GB free of ~1.1 TB) |\n| Services | es-http (ClusterIP :9200), es-cluster (headless :9300) |\n\n### 1.3 elasticsearch.yml (ConfigMap: es-config)\n\n```yaml\ncluster.name: es-cluster\nnode.name: ${POD_NAME}\nnode.roles: [ master, data, ingest ]\nnode.attr.tier: hot\nnetwork.host: 0.0.0.0\ndiscovery.seed_hosts:\n  - es-cluster-0.es-cluster\n  - es-cluster-1.es-cluster\n  - es-cluster-2.es-cluster\ncluster.initial_master_nodes:\n  - es-cluster-0\n  - es-cluster-1\n  - es-cluster-2\nnode.store.allow_mmap: false\nxpack.security.enabled: false\nxpack.security.http.ssl.enabled: false\nxpack.security.transport.ssl.enabled: false\n```\n\n### 1.4 Indices\n\n| Index | Shards | Replicas | Docs | Size | Notes |\n|-------|--------|----------|------|------|-------|\n| audit-index | 3 primary | 1 | 0 | 1.3 KB | routing.allocation.require.tier=hot; _tier_preference=data_content |\n\n**Shard placement (current):**\n\n| Shard | Primary node | Replica node |\n|-------|-------------|-------------|\n| audit-index/0 | es-cluster-2 | es-cluster-0 |\n| audit-index/1 | es-cluster-0 | es-cluster-1 |\n| audit-index/2 | es-cluster-2 | es-cluster-1 |\n\n### 1.5 Index Settings (Non-Default)\n\n`audit-index` has the following non-default allocation settings:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"index.routing.allocation.include._tier_preference\": \"data_content\",\n  \"index.routing.allocation.require.tier\": \"hot\"\n}\n```\n\n`require.tier: hot` hard-pins all shards to nodes bearing `node.attr.tier=hot`. All three current nodes carry this attribute, so the constraint is satisfied. During any topology change (adding non-hot nodes or removing the attribute), this constraint must be re-evaluated before shards will allocate.\n\n### 1.6 Cluster Settings\n\n- **Persistent settings:** none configured (all defaults)\n- **Transient settings:** none configured (all defaults)\n- Notable defaults active:\n  - `cluster.routing.allocation.disk.watermark.low: 85%`\n  - `cluster.routing.allocation.disk.watermark.high: 90%`\n  - `cluster.routing.allocation.disk.watermark.flood_stage: 95%`\n  - `cluster.max_shards_per_node: 1000`\n  - `action.destructive_requires_name: true`\n\n### 1.7 ILM Policies\n\nAll policies present are built-in managed policies (`_meta.managed: true`). **None are currently in use** by any index or data stream. Custom policies: none.\n\n| Policy | Hot rollover | Warm | Delete |\n|--------|-------------|------|--------|\n| .monitoring-8-ilm-policy | 3d / 50 GB | forcemerge | 3d |\n| behavioral_analytics-events-default_policy | 30d / 50 GB | 2d forcemerge+shrink | 180d |\n| ilm-history-ilm-policy | 30d / 50 GB | — | 90d |\n| ml-size-based-ilm-policy | 50 GB | — | — |\n\n### 1.8 Index Templates\n\nOnly built-in managed templates exist (`.kibana-reporting`, `.watch-history-16`, etc.). No custom index templates are present.\n\n### 1.9 Security\n\n| Setting | Value | Risk |\n|---------|-------|------|\n| xpack.security.enabled | **false** | CRITICAL — no authentication |\n| xpack.security.http.ssl.enabled | **false** | CRITICAL — plaintext HTTP |\n| xpack.security.transport.ssl.enabled | **false** | CRITICAL — plaintext inter-node |\n\nThe cluster is fully open: any pod in the cluster can read, write, or delete all data without credentials.\n\n### 1.10 Snapshot Repositories\n\n**None configured.** There is no backup target for the cluster.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Issues Requiring Action Before Upgrade\n\n### CRITICAL\n\n1. **No snapshot repository**: Upgrades are irreversible at the index compatibility level. A full snapshot must be taken and verified before any upgrade step is attempted.\n\n2. **Security disabled**: `xpack.security.enabled: false` is not acceptable for production. Enabling security requires a full rolling restart and TLS certificate provisioning. This should be done as a standalone change before the version upgrade to keep rollback windows clean.\n\n3. **`cluster.initial_master_nodes` still set**: This setting is only for first-time bootstrap and must be removed from `elasticsearch.yml` after initial cluster formation. Leaving it set can cause split-brain issues if a quorum is lost and nodes are restarted. It does not prevent normal operation but creates operational risk.\n\n### HIGH\n\n4. **JVM heap at 512 MB**: Elasticsearch recommends heap ≤ 50% of available RAM, minimum 1 GB for production. At 2 Gi container limit, the recommended setting is `-Xms1g -Xmx1g`. At 512 MB, GC pressure increases significantly under any indexing load.\n\n5. **PVC at 5 Gi**: Currently near-empty, but 5 Gi is far below any production sizing for an audit log index. Plan for PVC expansion before data volume grows; PVC expansion requires StorageClass support for `allowVolumeExpansion`.\n\n6. **`updateStrategy: OnDelete`**: Rolling upgrades are fully manual — each pod must be deleted one at a time. Consider switching to `RollingUpdate` with `maxUnavailable: 1` for automated, ordered upgrades (requires Kubernetes 1.22+).\n\n### MEDIUM\n\n7. **All nodes are combined-role**: No dedicated master nodes. With 3 combined nodes, losing 2 simultaneously loses both quorum and all data capacity. For production, dedicated master-eligible nodes (3 or 5) with separate data nodes are recommended.\n\n8. **`node.store.allow_mmap: false`**: Disables memory-mapped files, which reduces performance. The `vm.max_map_count` kernel parameter (`sysctl -w vm.max_map_count=262144`) should be set via an `initContainer` or node configuration, then this flag should be removed to re-enable mmap.\n\n9. **No monitoring**: The `.monitoring-8-ilm-policy` policy exists but no monitoring data streams are active. Upgrade visibility requires monitoring of indexing rate, heap usage, GC time, and shard counts.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Migration Plan: Security Enablement (Pre-Upgrade)\n\n**Goal:** Enable xpack security and TLS without changing data or cluster version.  \n**Requires:** Rolling restart (one pod at a time); cluster stays green throughout.\n\n### Step 3.1 — Generate TLS certificates\n\n```bash\n# Run on a temporary pod or locally with elasticsearch-certutil\ndocker run --rm -v $(pwd)/certs:/certs \\\n  docker.elastic.co/elasticsearch/elasticsearch:8.11.1 \\\n  bin/elasticsearch-certutil ca --out /certs/elastic-stack-ca.p12 --pass \"\"\n\ndocker run --rm -v $(pwd)/certs:/certs \\\n  docker.elastic.co/elasticsearch/elasticsearch:8.11.1 \\\n  bin/elasticsearch-certutil cert --ca /certs/elastic-stack-ca.p12 --ca-pass \"\" \\\n  --out /certs/elastic-certificates.p12 --pass \"\"\n```\n\n### Step 3.2 — Create Kubernetes Secret\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n elasticsearch create secret generic es-certs \\\n  --from-file=elastic-certificates.p12=./certs/elastic-certificates.p12 \\\n  --from-file=elastic-stack-ca.p12=./certs/elastic-stack-ca.p12\n```\n\n### Step 3.3 — Update elasticsearch.yml ConfigMap\n\nRemove `cluster.initial_master_nodes` and enable security:\n\n```yaml\ncluster.name: es-cluster\nnode.name: ${POD_NAME}\nnode.roles: [ master, data, ingest ]\nnode.attr.tier: hot\nnetwork.host: 0.0.0.0\ndiscovery.seed_hosts:\n  - es-cluster-0.es-cluster\n  - es-cluster-1.es-cluster\n  - es-cluster-2.es-cluster\n# cluster.initial_master_nodes: REMOVED after initial bootstrap\nnode.store.allow_mmap: false\nxpack.security.enabled: true\nxpack.security.http.ssl.enabled: true\nxpack.security.http.ssl.keystore.path: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/elastic-certificates.p12\nxpack.security.transport.ssl.enabled: true\nxpack.security.transport.ssl.verification_mode: certificate\nxpack.security.transport.ssl.keystore.path: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/elastic-certificates.p12\nxpack.security.transport.ssl.truststore.path: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/elastic-stack-ca.p12\n```\n\n### Step 3.4 — Update StatefulSet to mount certs and fix heap\n\nAdd to the container spec:\n\n```yaml\nenv:\n- name: ES_JAVA_OPTS\n  value: \"-Xms1g -Xmx1g\"   # increased from 512m\nvolumeMounts:\n- name: es-certs\n  mountPath: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs\n  readOnly: true\nvolumes:\n- name: es-certs\n  secret:\n    secretName: es-certs\n```\n\n### Step 3.5 — Set built-in passwords (post-restart)\n\nAfter the first node restarts with security enabled, set the built-in user passwords:\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n elasticsearch exec es-cluster-0 -- \\\n  bin/elasticsearch-setup-passwords auto\n# Store output passwords in a secrets manager\n```\n\n### Step 3.6 — Rolling restart (OnDelete strategy)\n\n```bash\n# Delete one pod at a time; wait for green before proceeding to next\nkubectl -n elasticsearch delete pod es-cluster-2\n# Wait: kubectl -n elasticsearch exec curl-test -- \\\n#   curl -su elastic:<pass> \"https://es-http:9200/_cluster/health?wait_for_status=green&timeout=120s\"\nkubectl -n elasticsearch delete pod es-cluster-1\n# Wait for green\nkubectl -n elasticsearch delete pod es-cluster-0\n# Wait for green\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. Migration Plan: Version Upgrade 8.11.1 → 8.17.x\n\n**Target version:** 8.17.x (latest 8.x stable as of plan date)  \n**Minimum path:** Single-hop upgrade within 8.x is supported (no intermediate version needed).  \n**Wire compatibility:** 8.x nodes are wire-compatible with 7.17+ nodes. A mixed 8.x cluster is valid during rolling upgrade.\n\n### Step 4.1 — Prerequisite gate (all must pass)\n\n- [ ] Snapshot repository registered and snapshot verified restorable\n- [ ] Cluster health is green\n- [ ] No unassigned shards\n- [ ] Security enabled (TLS + authentication active)\n- [ ] `cluster.initial_master_nodes` removed from config\n- [ ] All pending tasks drained (`number_of_pending_tasks == 0`)\n- [ ] Deprecation API clean (no upgrade-blocking deprecations):\n\n```bash\ncurl -su elastic:<pass> \"https://es-http:9200/_migration/deprecations\"\n```\n\n### Step 4.2 — Disable shard rebalancing\n\n```bash\ncurl -su elastic:<pass> -X PUT \"https://es-http:9200/_cluster/settings\" \\\n  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{\n  \"persistent\": {\n    \"cluster.routing.allocation.enable\": \"primaries\"\n  }\n}'\n```\n\nThis prevents unnecessary shard movement during the rolling restart.\n\n### Step 4.3 — Update the StatefulSet image\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n elasticsearch set image statefulset/es-cluster \\\n  elasticsearch=docker.elastic.co/elasticsearch/elasticsearch:8.17.6\n```\n\nWith `updateStrategy: OnDelete`, this only updates the template — no pods restart yet.\n\n### Step 4.4 — Rolling pod replacement (one at a time)\n\nFor each node, starting with a non-master (any non-elected-master node):\n\n```bash\n# Identify current master first\ncurl -su elastic:<pass> \"https://es-http:9200/_cat/master?v\"\n\n# Upgrade non-master nodes first; master last\nkubectl -n elasticsearch delete pod es-cluster-2\n# Poll until green AND es-cluster-2 is back and running 8.17.x:\nkubectl -n elasticsearch exec curl-test -- \\\n  curl -su elastic:<pass> \\\n  \"https://es-http:9200/_cat/nodes?v&h=name,version,master\"\n# Repeat for es-cluster-1, then es-cluster-0 (if master)\n```\n\n### Step 4.5 — Re-enable shard allocation\n\n```bash\ncurl -su elastic:<pass> -X PUT \"https://es-http:9200/_cluster/settings\" \\\n  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{\n  \"persistent\": {\n    \"cluster.routing.allocation.enable\": null\n  }\n}'\n```\n\n### Step 4.6 — Post-upgrade validation\n\n```bash\n# All nodes on new version\ncurl -su elastic:<pass> \"https://es-http:9200/_cat/nodes?v&h=name,version,master\"\n\n# Cluster health green\ncurl -su elastic:<pass> \"https://es-http:9200/_cluster/health?pretty\"\n\n# audit-index still has all shards allocated\ncurl -su elastic:<pass> \"https://es-http:9200/_cat/shards?v\"\n\n# Index settings preserved\ncurl -su elastic:<pass> \"https://es-http:9200/audit-index/_settings?pretty\"\n\n# No deprecation warnings blocking future upgrades\ncurl -su elastic:<pass> \"https://es-http:9200/_migration/deprecations\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. Additional Recommended Changes (Post-Upgrade)\n\n### 5.1 Switch UpdateStrategy to RollingUpdate\n\n```yaml\nupdateStrategy:\n  type: RollingUpdate\n  rollingUpdate:\n    maxUnavailable: 1\n```\n\nThis enables ordered, automated rolling upgrades in future cycles.\n\n### 5.2 Enable mmap for performance\n\nAdd an `initContainer` to set the kernel parameter:\n\n```yaml\ninitContainers:\n- name: set-vm-max-map-count\n  image: busybox\n  command: ['sysctl', '-w', 'vm.max_map_count=262144']\n  securityContext:\n    privileged: true\n```\n\nThen remove `node.store.allow_mmap: false` from elasticsearch.yml.\n\n### 5.3 Register a snapshot repository\n\nBefore any future upgrade, register a repository (S3, GCS, or a shared PVC):\n\n```bash\ncurl -su elastic:<pass> -X PUT \"https://es-http:9200/_snapshot/backups\" \\\n  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{\n  \"type\": \"fs\",\n  \"settings\": {\n    \"location\": \"/mnt/snapshots\"\n  }\n}'\n```\n\nCreate a Snapshot Lifecycle Management (SLM) policy for daily automated snapshots.\n\n### 5.4 Assign an ILM policy to audit-index\n\nCurrently `audit-index` has no ILM lifecycle. An audit index will grow unbounded. Assign a policy that rolls over at size/age and deletes old indices:\n\n```bash\n# Create policy\ncurl -su elastic:<pass> -X PUT \"https://es-http:9200/_ilm/policy/audit-policy\" \\\n  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{\n  \"policy\": {\n    \"phases\": {\n      \"hot\": { \"actions\": { \"rollover\": { \"max_age\": \"30d\", \"max_primary_shard_size\": \"10gb\" } } },\n      \"delete\": { \"min_age\": \"90d\", \"actions\": { \"delete\": {} } }\n    }\n  }\n}'\n# Apply to index template for audit-index\n```\n\n### 5.5 PVC expansion planning\n\nPVC expansion (if StorageClass supports it) can be done in-place:\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n elasticsearch patch pvc data-es-cluster-0 \\\n  -p '{\"spec\":{\"resources\":{\"requests\":{\"storage\":\"50Gi\"}}}}'\n# Repeat for data-es-cluster-1, data-es-cluster-2\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. Risk Assessment\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|-----------|--------|-----------|\n| Shard unavailability during restart | Low | Medium | OnDelete strategy, wait-for-green between pods |\n| Data loss on upgrade failure | Low | High | Snapshot before any change; verify restore |\n| Security enablement causes auth failure | Medium | High | Test with one pod first; keep a known-good password reference |\n| PVC too small for audit data growth | High | Medium | Plan expansion before index grows; 5 Gi is near-empty now |\n| Split-brain from initial_master_nodes misconfiguration | Low | Critical | Remove setting from config in Step 3.3 |\n| JVM GC pauses under load at 512m heap | High | Medium | Increase to 1g in same config change as security |\n\n---\n\n## 7. Rollback Plan\n\n### Rollback from security change\n\nRevert the es-config ConfigMap to the original (security disabled), delete each pod one at a time. Cluster will restart without authentication.\n\n### Rollback from version upgrade\n\nElasticsearch does **not** support downgrading a node once data has been written with a newer Lucene version. The only rollback path is:\n\n1. Stop all 8.17.x pods.\n2. Restore from the pre-upgrade snapshot into a fresh 8.11.1 cluster.\n3. This is why Step 4.1 (snapshot gate) is non-negotiable.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Change Order Summary\n\n| # | Change | Type | Requires Restart | Approval Gate |\n|---|--------|------|-----------------|---------------|\n| 1 | Configure snapshot repository + take snapshot | Live API | No | SRE lead |\n| 2 | Remove cluster.initial_master_nodes from config | Config change | Yes (rolling) | SRE lead |\n| 3 | Increase JVM heap to 1g | Config change | Yes (rolling) | SRE lead |\n| 4 | Provision TLS certs + enable xpack.security | Config + Secret | Yes (rolling) | Security team + SRE lead |\n| 5 | Set built-in user passwords | API call | No | SRE lead |\n| 6 | Upgrade image 8.11.1 → 8.17.x | Image update | Yes (rolling) | Change advisory board |\n| 7 | Enable mmap via initContainer | Config + STS | Yes (rolling) | SRE lead |\n| 8 | Switch to RollingUpdate strategy | STS spec | No | SRE lead |\n| 9 | Add ILM policy to audit-index | API call | No | SRE lead |\n| 10 | Expand PVCs | PVC patch | No | Storage team |\n\n---\n\n*This plan is for review only. No changes have been or will be applied to the live cluster until this document is approved by the SRE lead and, for changes 4 and 6, the relevant approval gates.*","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
