{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_0131Kia88bPfsuTq1Wxao3cq","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01EsTXn2BgQAaYUVur2yTheA","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/tmp/mongo-plan.md","content":"# MongoDB Replica Set — Change / Migration Plan\n\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-24\n**Namespace:** `mongodb`\n**Replica Set:** `mongodb-replica`\n**Status:** REVIEW ONLY — no changes have been applied.\nThe live cluster must remain exactly as found until this plan is approved.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current State\n\n### 1.1 Replica Set Topology\n\n| Property | Value |\n|---|---|\n| Replica-set name | `mongodb-replica` |\n| Member count | 3 (all data-bearing, no arbiters) |\n| Protocol version | 1 (Raft) |\n| `writeConcernMajorityJournalDefault` | `true` |\n\n**Members** (equal priority = 1, votes = 1, not hidden):\n\n| `_id` | FQDN host |\n|---|---|\n| 0 | `mongodb-replica-0.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017` |\n| 1 | `mongodb-replica-1.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017` |\n| 2 | `mongodb-replica-2.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017` |\n\n**Replica-set settings (current):**\n\n| Setting | Current value |\n|---|---|\n| `heartbeatIntervalMillis` | 2000 |\n| `heartbeatTimeoutSecs` | 10 |\n| `electionTimeoutMillis` | 10000 |\n| `catchUpTimeoutMillis` | -1 (unlimited) |\n| `chainingAllowed` | `true` |\n| `getLastErrorDefaults` | `{ w: 1, wtimeout: 0 }` |\n\n### 1.2 Mongod Configuration (ConfigMap `mongod-config`)\n\n| Category | Parameter | Current value |\n|---|---|---|\n| Storage / WiredTiger | `journalCompressor` | `zlib` |\n| Storage | `dbPath` | `/data/db` |\n| Network | `bindIpAll` | `true` |\n| Replication | `replSetName` | `mongodb-replica` |\n| Security | `authorization` | `enabled` |\n| Security | `keyFile` | `/etc/mongo-keyfile/keyfile` |\n| System log | `verbosity` | `1` (raised from default 0) |\n| Operation profiling | `mode` | `slowOp` |\n| Operation profiling | `slowOpThresholdMs` | `200` ms (tightened from MongoDB default of 100 ms) |\n\n### 1.3 Users and Roles\n\n| User | Auth DB | Roles | Auth mechanisms |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `admin-user` | `admin` | `clusterAdmin`, `userAdminAnyDatabase`, `readWriteAnyDatabase` | `SCRAM-SHA-1`, `SCRAM-SHA-256` |\n\nOnly one user exists. The account combines cluster-admin, user-admin, and\nfull read-write access — there is no least-privilege separation.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Target Hardened Baseline\n\nThe following table describes the desired target state. Rows marked **CHANGE**\nrequire action in the change window.\n\n| Area | Parameter | Current | Target | Action |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| Network binding | `bindIpAll` | `true` | restrict to loopback + pod IP | **CHANGE** |\n| TLS | `net.tls` | absent | `requireTLS` for all client and intra-cluster traffic | **CHANGE** |\n| Auth mechanisms | SCRAM-SHA-1 | enabled (present on `admin-user`) | disabled cluster-wide | **CHANGE** |\n| System log | `verbosity` | `1` | `0` (default — production-quiet) | **CHANGE** |\n| Operation profiling | `slowOpThresholdMs` | `200` ms | `100` ms (MongoDB default) | **CHANGE** |\n| Write concern | `getLastErrorDefaults.w` | `1` | `\"majority\"` | **CHANGE** |\n| Write concern | `getLastErrorDefaults.wtimeout` | `0` (unlimited) | `5000` ms | **CHANGE** |\n| Catch-up | `catchUpTimeoutMillis` | `-1` (unlimited) | `30000` ms | **CHANGE** |\n| Role separation | `admin-user` roles | combined superuser | split: dedicated DBA + per-app accounts | **CHANGE** |\n| Journal compressor | `journalCompressor` | `zlib` | `snappy` (lower CPU overhead) | **CHANGE** (conditional — see note) |\n\n---\n\n## 3. Migration Steps\n\nExecute steps in the order shown during the scheduled change window.\nEach step includes a verification check and an individual rollback.\n\n### Step 1 — Disable SCRAM-SHA-1 on existing users\n\nSCRAM-SHA-1 uses SHA-1, which is weaker than SHA-256. Remove it from `admin-user`\nand enforce `SCRAM-SHA-256` cluster-wide.\n\n**Action (run once on primary):**\n\n```javascript\n// Remove SCRAM-SHA-1 credential from the existing admin account\ndb.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").updateUser(\"admin-user\", {\n  mechanisms: [\"SCRAM-SHA-256\"]\n})\n```\n\nAdd the following to `mongod.conf` under the `security:` block, then apply via\nrolling restart (Step 6):\n\n```yaml\nsecurity:\n  authorization: enabled\n  keyFile: /etc/mongo-keyfile/keyfile\n  authenticationMechanisms: SCRAM-SHA-256\n```\n\n**Verify:**\n```javascript\ndb.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").system.users.find({user:\"admin-user\"},{credentials:1})\n// Expected: only \"SCRAM-SHA-256\" key present under credentials\n```\n\n**Rollback:** Re-add SCRAM-SHA-1 via `updateUser` with `mechanisms: [\"SCRAM-SHA-1\",\"SCRAM-SHA-256\"]`;\nremove `authenticationMechanisms` from config; rolling restart.\n\n---\n\n### Step 2 — Provision TLS Certificates\n\nCreate a TLS Secret containing a CA certificate, a server certificate with SANs\ncovering all pod DNS names, and the private key. Mount it into each pod.\n\n**Action:**\n\n```bash\n# Generate or obtain certs with SANs for all three pod hostnames:\n#   mongodb-replica-0.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local\n#   mongodb-replica-1.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local\n#   mongodb-replica-2.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local\n\nkubectl -n mongodb create secret generic mongo-tls \\\n  --from-file=tls.pem=<combined-cert-and-key.pem> \\\n  --from-file=ca.crt=<ca-cert.crt>\n```\n\nAdd a `volumeMount` to the StatefulSet pod spec:\n\n```yaml\nvolumeMounts:\n- name: mongo-tls\n  mountPath: /etc/mongo-tls\n  readOnly: true\nvolumes:\n- name: mongo-tls\n  secret:\n    secretName: mongo-tls\n```\n\n**Rollback:** Remove the `net.tls` block and the volume mount; rolling restart.\n\n---\n\n### Step 3 — Enable TLS and Restrict Network Binding\n\nReplace `bindIpAll: true` with an explicit bind address and add the TLS block.\n\nUpdate `mongod.conf`:\n\n```yaml\nnet:\n  bindIp: \"127.0.0.1\"   # mongod automatically also binds on the pod IP for intra-cluster when TLS is active\n  tls:\n    mode: requireTLS\n    certificateKeyFile: /etc/mongo-tls/tls.pem\n    CAFile: /etc/mongo-tls/ca.crt\n```\n\nIf TLS is not being added in the same window, restrict binding using the\nKubernetes Downward API to expose the pod IP:\n\n```yaml\n# StatefulSet env:\n- name: MY_POD_IP\n  valueFrom:\n    fieldRef:\n      fieldPath: status.podIP\n```\n\n```yaml\n# mongod.conf\nnet:\n  bindIp: \"127.0.0.1,$(MY_POD_IP)\"\n```\n\nApply via rolling restart (Step 6).\n\n**Rollback:** Restore `bindIpAll: true`, remove `net.tls`; rolling restart.\n\n---\n\n### Step 4 — Tighten Write-Concern and Catch-Up Defaults\n\nThese are in-memory replica-set settings; `rs.reconfig()` applies them without a\nrolling restart.\n\n**Action (run on primary):**\n\n```javascript\ncfg = rs.conf()\ncfg.settings.getLastErrorDefaults = { w: \"majority\", wtimeout: 5000 }\ncfg.settings.catchUpTimeoutMillis = 30000\nrs.reconfig(cfg)\n```\n\n**Verify:**\n\n```javascript\nrs.conf().settings\n// Expected: getLastErrorDefaults.w == \"majority\", wtimeout == 5000,\n//           catchUpTimeoutMillis == 30000\n```\n\n**Rollback:**\n\n```javascript\ncfg = rs.conf()\ncfg.settings.getLastErrorDefaults = { w: 1, wtimeout: 0 }\ncfg.settings.catchUpTimeoutMillis = -1\nrs.reconfig(cfg)\n```\n\n---\n\n### Step 5 — Separate Admin and Application Users (Least Privilege)\n\n`admin-user` currently holds `clusterAdmin`, `userAdminAnyDatabase`, and\n`readWriteAnyDatabase`. This violates least privilege. Split into:\n\n- A dedicated DBA account for cluster and user administration only.\n- A per-application service account with access only to its own database.\n- Reduce `admin-user` to a transitional fallback, then remove it once applications\n  are migrated to the new accounts.\n\n**Action (run on primary):**\n\n```javascript\n// 1. Create a DBA account (admin actions only)\ndb.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").createUser({\n  user: \"dba\",\n  pwd: \"<generate-with-strong-random>\",\n  mechanisms: [\"SCRAM-SHA-256\"],\n  roles: [\n    { role: \"clusterAdmin\",         db: \"admin\" },\n    { role: \"userAdminAnyDatabase\", db: \"admin\" }\n  ]\n})\n\n// 2. Create a per-application service account (example database \"myapp\")\ndb.getSiblingDB(\"myapp\").createUser({\n  user: \"myapp-svc\",\n  pwd: \"<generate-with-strong-random>\",\n  mechanisms: [\"SCRAM-SHA-256\"],\n  roles: [{ role: \"readWrite\", db: \"myapp\" }]\n})\n\n// 3. After confirming new accounts work, strip readWriteAnyDatabase from admin-user\ndb.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").updateUser(\"admin-user\", {\n  roles: [\n    { role: \"clusterAdmin\",         db: \"admin\" },\n    { role: \"userAdminAnyDatabase\", db: \"admin\" }\n  ]\n})\n```\n\nStore the new credentials in Kubernetes Secrets and update application connection\nstrings before removing `readWriteAnyDatabase` from `admin-user`.\n\n**Verify:**\n\n```javascript\ndb.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").system.users.find({},{user:1, roles:1})\n// Expected: admin-user has no readWriteAnyDatabase; dba and myapp-svc present\n```\n\n**Rollback:** Re-add `readWriteAnyDatabase` to `admin-user`; drop new accounts.\n\n---\n\n### Step 6 — Update ConfigMap and Perform Rolling Restart\n\nAfter Steps 1–3 config changes are finalised, apply the updated `mongod-config`\nConfigMap. The full target `mongod.conf`:\n\n```yaml\nstorage:\n  dbPath: /data/db\n  wiredTiger:\n    engineConfig:\n      journalCompressor: snappy        # changed from zlib — see Step 7 note\n\nnet:\n  bindIp: \"127.0.0.1\"                 # Step 3 — no longer bindIpAll\n  tls:\n    mode: requireTLS                   # Step 2\n    certificateKeyFile: /etc/mongo-tls/tls.pem\n    CAFile: /etc/mongo-tls/ca.crt\n\nreplication:\n  replSetName: mongodb-replica\n\nsecurity:\n  authorization: enabled\n  keyFile: /etc/mongo-keyfile/keyfile\n  authenticationMechanisms: SCRAM-SHA-256   # Step 1\n\nsystemLog:\n  verbosity: 0                         # changed from 1 — production default\n\noperationProfiling:\n  mode: slowOp\n  slowOpThresholdMs: 100               # changed from 200 — MongoDB default\n```\n\nApply the rolling restart (Kubernetes rolls pods in reverse order: 2 → 1 → 0;\npod-0 is typically primary and will be restarted last, triggering one election):\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n mongodb rollout restart statefulset/mongodb-replica\nkubectl -n mongodb rollout status statefulset/mongodb-replica\n```\n\n**Verify after each pod rejoins:**\n\n```javascript\nrs.status()\n// All members must show state PRIMARY or SECONDARY (not RECOVERING for > 30 s)\ndb.adminCommand({ ping: 1 })\n```\n\n**Rollback:** Re-apply the original ConfigMap data; rolling restart.\n\n---\n\n### Step 7 — (Conditional) Switch Journal Compressor to snappy\n\n`zlib` provides better compression ratios than `snappy` but at higher CPU cost.\nIf CPU profiling during and after the Step 6 restart shows acceptable overhead,\nkeep `zlib`. If CPU is a bottleneck, change `journalCompressor: zlib` to\n`journalCompressor: snappy` in the ConfigMap and perform another rolling restart.\n\n> **Note:** WiredTiger applies the new compressor only to newly written journal\n> files; existing journal files are not re-compressed.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Risk Assessment\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Auth failure after disabling SCRAM-SHA-1 | Low | High | Verify connection with SCRAM-SHA-256 before removing SHA-1 |\n| TLS cert SAN mismatch causes intra-cluster auth failure | Medium | High | Validate cert SANs against pod DNS names in a test namespace first |\n| Election during rolling restart | Certain (once) | Low | Replica set remains available; one brief primary election is expected |\n| `majority` write concern increases latency | Low | Low | Monitor P99 write latency; fall back to `w:1` if unacceptable |\n| `catchUpTimeoutMillis` bound causes data lag after failover | Low | Low | `majority` write concern already ensures durability on 2+ nodes |\n| `snappy` compressor increases journal size | Low | Low | Monitor disk usage for one week post-change |\n\n---\n\n## 5. Rollback Summary\n\n| Step | Rollback action |\n|---|---|\n| 1 — SCRAM-SHA-1 | `updateUser` to restore SCRAM-SHA-1; remove `authenticationMechanisms` from config; rolling restart |\n| 2 — TLS certs | Remove Secret, volume mount from StatefulSet |\n| 3 — bindIp / TLS in config | Restore `bindIpAll: true`, remove `net.tls`; rolling restart |\n| 4 — write-concern / catch-up | `rs.reconfig()` restoring original `getLastErrorDefaults` and `catchUpTimeoutMillis: -1` |\n| 5 — user separation | Re-add `readWriteAnyDatabase` to `admin-user`; drop new accounts if unused |\n| 6 — ConfigMap + rolling restart | Re-apply original ConfigMap; rolling restart |\n| 7 — journal compressor | Revert `journalCompressor` to `zlib`; rolling restart |\n\n---\n\n## 6. Change Order Summary\n\n| # | Change | Requires restart | Approval gate |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 | Disable SCRAM-SHA-1 on `admin-user` | Yes (config change + rolling restart in step 6) | DBA lead |\n| 2 | Provision TLS Secret and StatefulSet volume mount | Yes (StatefulSet update) | SRE lead |\n| 3 | Enable TLS + restrict `bindIp` in config | Yes (rolling restart in step 6) | SRE lead |\n| 4 | Set `getLastErrorDefaults` to `majority/5000` and bound `catchUpTimeoutMillis` | No (rs.reconfig) | DBA lead |\n| 5 | Create `dba` + app service accounts; strip `readWriteAnyDatabase` from `admin-user` | No | DBA lead + app team |\n| 6 | Apply updated ConfigMap + rolling restart | Yes | Change advisory board |\n| 7 | Switch journal compressor to `snappy` (conditional) | Yes (second rolling restart) | SRE lead |\n\n---\n\n*This document is for review only. No live changes have been or will be applied\nuntil the plan is approved by all required gates.*\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_