tional fallback, then remove it once applications\n  are migrated to the new accounts.\n\n**Action (run on primary):**\n\n```javascript\n// 1. Create a DBA account (admin actions only)\ndb.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").createUser({\n  user: \"dba\",\n  pwd: \"<generate-with-strong-random>\",\n  mechanisms: [\"SCRAM-SHA-256\"],\n  roles: [\n    { role: \"clusterAdmin\",         db: \"admin\" },\n    { role: \"userAdminAnyDatabase\", db: \"admin\" }\n  ]\n})\n\n// 2. Create a per-application service account (example database \"myapp\")\ndb.getSiblingDB(\"myapp\").createUser({\n  user: \"myapp-svc\",\n  pwd: \"<generate-with-strong-random>\",\n  mechanisms: [\"SCRAM-SHA-256\"],\n  roles: [{ role: \"readWrite\", db: \"myapp\" }]\n})\n\n// 3. After confirming new accounts work, strip readWriteAnyDatabase from admin-user\ndb.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").updateUser(\"admin-user\", {\n  roles: [\n    { role: \"clusterAdmin\",         db: \"admin\" },\n    { role: \"userAdminAnyDatabase\", db: \"admin\" }\n  ]\n})\n```\n\nStore the new credentials in Kubernetes Secrets and update application connection\nstrings before removing `readWriteAnyDatabase` from `admin-user`.\n\n**Verify:**\n\n```javascript\ndb.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").system.users.find({},{user:1, roles:1})\n// Expected: admin-user has no readWriteAnyDatabase; dba and myapp-svc present\n```\n\n**Rollback:** Re-add `readWriteAnyDatabase` to `admin-user`; drop new accounts.\n\n---\n\n### Step 6 — Update ConfigMap and Perform Rolling Restart\n\nAfter Steps 1–3 config changes are finalised, apply the updated `mongod-config`\nConfigMap. The full target `mongod.conf`:\n\n```yaml\nstorage:\n  dbPath: /data/db\n  wiredTiger:\n    engineConfig:\n      journalCompressor: snappy        # changed from zlib — see Step 7 note\n\nnet:\n  bindIp: \"127.0.0.1\"                 # Step 3 — no longer bindIpAll\n  tls:\n    mode: requireTLS                   # Step 2\n    certificateKeyFile: /etc/mongo-tls/tls.pem\n    CAFile: /etc/mongo-tls/ca.cr