write concern increases latency | Low | Low | Monitor P99 write latency; fall back to `w:1` if unacceptable |\n| `catchUpTimeoutMillis` bound causes data lag after failover | Low | Low | `majority` write concern already ensures durability on 2+ nodes |\n| `snappy` compressor increases journal size | Low | Low | Monitor disk usage for one week post-change |\n\n---\n\n## 5. Rollback Summary\n\n| Step | Rollback action |\n|---|---|\n| 1 — SCRAM-SHA-1 | `updateUser` to restore SCRAM-SHA-1; remove `authenticationMechanisms` from config; rolling restart |\n| 2 — TLS certs | Remove Secret, volume mount from StatefulSet |\n| 3 — bindIp / TLS in config | Restore `bindIpAll: true`, remove `net.tls`; rolling restart |\n| 4 — write-concern / catch-up | `rs.reconfig()` restoring original `getLastErrorDefaults` and `catchUpTimeoutMillis: -1` |\n| 5 — user separation | Re-add `readWriteAnyDatabase` to `admin-user`; drop new accounts if unused |\n| 6 — ConfigMap + rolling restart | Re-apply original ConfigMap; rolling restart |\n| 7 — journal compressor | Revert `journalCompressor` to `zlib`; rolling restart |\n\n---\n\n## 6. Change Order Summary\n\n| # | Change | Requires restart | Approval gate |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 | Disable SCRAM-SHA-1 on `admin-user` | Yes (config change + rolling restart in step 6) | DBA lead |\n| 2 | Provision TLS Secret and StatefulSet volume mount | Yes (StatefulSet update) | SRE lead |\n| 3 | Enable TLS + restrict `bindIp` in config | Yes (rolling restart in step 6) | SRE lead |\n| 4 | Set `getLastErrorDefaults` to `majority/5000` and bound `catchUpTimeoutMillis` | No (rs.reconfig) | DBA lead |\n| 5 | Create `dba` + app service accounts; strip `readWriteAnyDatabase` from `admin-user` | No | DBA lead + app team |\n| 6 | Apply updated ConfigMap + rolling restart | Yes | Change advisory board |\n| 7 | Switch journal compressor to `snappy` (conditional) | Yes (second rolling restart) | SRE lead |\n\n---\n\n*This document is for review only. No live changes have been or will be applied\nuntil the plan is approved by all required gates.*\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null,"userModified":false}}
